`config.bst` at the project root controls build settings with strict keys.

### A minimal config

[codeblock, $code("bst"):
    project #= "html"
    entry_root #= "src"
]

### Strict keys

Only known config keys are accepted. Unknown keys are rejected. Every value must fold at compile time.

Common keys:

- `project`: selects the builder, currently only `"html"`.
- `entry_root`: the source folder, usually `"src"`.
- `package_folders`: where to find project-local source-backed packages. Defaults to `lib` when omitted.
- `dev_folder` and `output_folder`: where builds are written.

### Remember

- Only `config.bst` has config semantics.
- Values must be compile-time constants.
- HTML-specific settings belong to the HTML builder.
